Create Bridge Tables and Populate the Tables 12

We are going to create 2 bridge tables in the data warehouse: MarketSubMarketBrdige table and RegionSubRegionBridge table.

Click  and download the SQL files to create bridge tables.



*Using SSIS Toolbox, the following components will be drag in the Control Flow Dashboard:

Step 1: Drag and drop Data Flow Task transformation from the SSIS Toolbox on the right.

Step 2: Double click on Data Flow Task, then drag and drop OLE DB Source.

Step 3: Double click on OLE DB Source. Inside the OLE DB Source Editor, choose SQL Command.

Step 4: Put the below query inside sql command as the source.


SELECT distinct  MarketName, CBSA, PropertyType, [QuarterlyDate], e.[DayKey]
FROM [MarketDatamart_Staging].[dbo].[SubMarketVsMarket By PropertyTypes] A
LEFT JOIN  [MarketDatamart_Staging].[dbo].[Vw_AllFips] B ON A.MarketName = B.RCAName
LEFT JOIN [MarketDatamart_Staging].[dbo].[All_Fundamental]C ON B.RCAName = C.MSA
LEFT JOIN [MarketDatamart_Staging].[dbo].[AllPivot] D ON C.MSA = D.Metro
 join [MarketDatamart_Staging].[dbo].[DimCalendarDay] e on d.QuarterlyDate = e.CalendarDate
WHERE CBSA IS NOT NULL


Step 5: Drag and drop 3 Look Up transformations.

First Look Up Transformation

Step 6: Double click on the Look Up transformation and in General pane, set to Full Cache, OLE DB Connection Manager, and Ignore Failure.

Step 7: In the Connection pane, set appropriate OLE DB Connection Manger and choose DimBusinessPropertyType table.

Step 8: In the Columns pane, connect PropertyType from the source to the BusinessPropertyType on the DimBusinessPropertyType table, and bring the PropertyKey as output.

Second Look Up Transformation

Step 9: Same as Step 6 as above.

Step 10: In the Connection pane, set appropriate OLE DB Connection Manger and choose DimMarket table.

Step 11: In the Columns pane, connect MarketName from the source to the MarketName on the DimMarket table, and bring the MarketKey as output.

Third Look Up Transformation

Step 12: Same as Step 6 as above.

Step 13: In the Connection pane, set appropriate OLE DB Connection Manager and choose DimSubMarket table.

Step 14: In the Columns pane, connect PropertyKey from the source to the PropertyKey on the DimSubMarket table, and bring the SubMarketKey as output.

Load to the Destination Table

Step 15: Drag and drop OLEDB Destination.

Step 16: Double click the OLE DB Destination to edit. Connect to OLE DB Connection Manager and choose the bridge table that we already created called MarketSubMarketBridge and map the columns to insert new records into the destination table.



The Populated Bridge tables after executing the package.

There will be times when you arrive at a many to many relationships between a fact and a dimension. These many to many relationships are in violation of the dimensional modeling rules, so how do you handle this multi-valued relationship?  Bridge tables. A bridge table is used to bridge the gap between a fact table and a dimension at a lower grain.
